        "title": "Simplify",
        "text": "$$\\frac{\\frac{\\sin(x)}{\\cos(x)}+\\frac{\\cos(x)}{\\sin(x)}}{\\frac{1}{\\sin(x)}}=\\sin(x)\\left(\\frac{\\sin(x)}{\\cos(x)}+\\frac{\\cos(x)}{\\sin(x)}\\right)=\\frac{\\sin**2(x)}{\\cos(x)}+\\cos(x)$$",
        "variabilization": {},
